# Customer Order Management API

This is a simple RESTful API built with Go (Golang) using the Echo framework. It demonstrates a basic customer and order management system, along with authentication using JWT tokens. The API follows the MVC pattern and clean architecture principles.

## Features

- Customer Management
  - Get customers with pagination
  - Get customer details
  - Insert new customer
  - Update existing customer
  - Delete customer
  - Search customers

- Order Management
  - Get orders with pagination
  - Get order details
  - Insert new order
  - Update existing order
  - Delete order
  - Search orders

- Authentication Management
  - Get login data
  - Insert login data

- JWT token-based authentication for secure endpoints


## Prerequisites

- [Go](https://golang.org/dl/) 1.18 or later
- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/get-started)
- [Docker Compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)

## Setup

1. **Clone the repository:**

   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/project.git
   cd project

2. **Run the application using Docker Compose:**

    ```sh
    docker-compose up --build

3. **Run database migrations:**

    ```sh
    docker exec -it api /bin/sh -c "go run database/migration.go"

